      • pageChanged

        public final void pageChanged(java.lang.Object changedProperty)
        Description copied from interface: IYRCPanelHolder
        Utility method invoked when ever interested views/components should update themselves to reflect the latest state of the editor.

        This method can also be invoked programatically using YRCBaseBehavior.pageChanged() .

        This method is invoked by infrastructure in the following scernarios:
        • Editor gets focus.
        • New task is shown in an editor.
        • New wizard page is shown with in a currently running task.
        Specified by:
        pageChanged in interface IYRCPanelHolder
        See Also:
        IYRCPanelHolder.pageChanged(Object)

      • panelModified

        public void panelModified(boolean isDirty)
        Description copied from interface: IYRCPanelHolder
        Utility method invoked when ever a editor needs to be updated, to reflect the state of its contents.

        Usually invoked when there are changes being performed in the current editor.
        Specified by:
        panelModified in interface IYRCPanelHolder
